catalog insert --id "ERX311347" --paths "/sysdev/s9/bruno/acoel_phylo/data/ERR338470_1.fastq.gz:/sysdev/s9/bruno/acoel_phylo/data/ERR338470_2.fastq.gz" --species "Eupolybothrus sp. PS-2013" --ncbi_id "1391732" --library_id "ERR338470" --library_type "TRANSCRIPTOMIC" --sequencer "Illumina HiSeq 2000" --seq_center "GigaScience" --note "Protocols: Manual collection of specimen from natural habitat (cave), crushed and preserved in liquid RNA-later (Qiagen, USA). Total RNA was extract using TRIzol reagent (Invitrogen, USA) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Messenger RNA (mRNA) was isolated from total RNA using the Dynabeads mRNA Purification Kit (Invitrogen, Carlsbad Ca.USA). The mRNA was fragmented and transcribed into first-strand cDNA using SuperScript(tm) II Reverse Transcriptase (Invitrogen, Carlsbad Ca. USA) and N6 primer (IDT). RNase H (Invitrogen, Carlsbad Ca. USA) and DNA polymerase I (Invitrogen, Shanghai ChinaNew England BioLabs) were subsequently applied to synthesize the second-strand cDNA. The double-stranded cDNA then underwent end-repair, a single 'A' base addition, adapter ligation, and size selection (~250bp), indexed and PCR amplification to construct library." --sample_prep "Transcriptome analysis of the newly described centipede Eupolybothrus cavernicolus sp.n."
